# Documentation Updates

After **completed** work, update:

| File | When |
|------|------|
| `docs/WORKLOG.md` | Always — date, done/changed/blocked/next |
| `docs/TASKS.md` | Always — mark tasks done or add new ones |
| `docs/tasks/PHASE-*.md` | When work maps to a phase checklist item |
| `docs/DECISIONS.md` | Only when a product or technical decision changed |
| `docs/CHANGELOG.md` | Only when user-visible behavior changed |
| `docs/PROCESS.md` | Only when workflow or Definition of Done changed |

Do not update DECISIONS/CHANGELOG/PROCESS for routine implementation work.

Use the **process-updater** skill (`.cursor/skills/process-updater/SKILL.md`) or **update-process-docs** command for consistency.


# Extra Documentation Update Rules

After every completed implementation task, update:

- docs/WORKLOG.md:
  - date
  - task title
  - summary
  - files changed
  - checks/tests run
  - known issues
  - next suggested step

- docs/TASKS.md:
  - mark completed items
  - update in-progress items
  - add newly discovered tasks
  - mark blocked items

Update docs/DECISIONS.md only if:
- product scope changed
- architecture changed
- data model changed
- integration strategy changed
- security/privacy decision changed

Update docs/CHANGELOG.md only if:
- user-visible behavior changed
- feature added
- feature removed
- bug fixed

Do not change application code when the user only asks to update process docs.